    <h1>GDPR Compliance Statement</h1>
    <p>
      Student Assistant is committed to ensuring the protection of personal data
      and the privacy of our users. We adhere strictly to the guidelines set out
      by the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), effective as of May 25,
      2018.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Personal Data We Collect</h2>
    <p>
      At Student Assistant, we collect personal data to enhance our services and
      improve the learning experience. The types of data we collect include:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Contact Information: such as your name, email address, and telephone
        number.
      </li>
      <li>
        Account Details: username, password (encrypted), and other identifiers.
      </li>
      <li>
        Performance Data: to personalize learning experiences and adjust
        challenges.
      </li>
      <li>
        Usage Data: information on how you interact with our services, which
        helps us tailor content and improve functionality.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Your Data</h2>
    <p>Your personal data is used to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Provide, operate, and maintain our services.</li>
      <li>Enhance, personalize, and expand our services.</li>
      <li>Understand and analyze how you use our services.</li>
      <li>Develop new products, services, features, and functionality.</li>
      <li>
        Communicate with you, either directly or through one of our partners,
        including for customer service, to provide you with updates and other
        information relating to the website, and for marketing and promotional
        purposes.
      </li>
      <li>
        Send you emails and other communications that you have opted into.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
    <p>Student Assistant may share your data with:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Service providers who perform services for us and help us operate our
        business (e.g., hosting, analytics, email delivery, and database
        management services).
      </li>
      <li>
        Third parties if we believe that disclosure is advisable or necessary to
        comply with the law, enforce our terms of use, or protect the rights,
        property, or safety of Student Assistant or others.
      </li>
      <li>
        Potential buyers or other successors in the event of a merger,
        divestiture, restructuring, reorganization, dissolution, or other sale
        or transfer of some or all of Student Assistant's assets.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Data Protection Rights</h2>
    <p>Under GDPR, you have the following data protection rights:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        The right to access, update, or delete the information we have on you.
      </li>
      <li>The right of rectification.</li>
      <li>The right to object.</li>
      <li>The right of restriction.</li>
      <li>The right to data portability</li>
      <li>The right to withdraw consent.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      You can exercise these rights by contacting us directly. We will consider
      your request in accordance with applicable laws.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
    <p>
      We use appropriate technical and organizational security measures designed
      to protect the security of any personal information we process. However,
      please also remember that we cannot guarantee that the internet itself is
      100% secure.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update our GDPR Compliance Statement from time to time. We will
      notify you of any changes by posting the new policy on this page.
    </p>

